♫ ♫

00:01:20.340 --> 00:01:24.240
♫ ♫

00:01:24.240 --> 00:01:26.290
♫ ♫

00:01:26.290 --> 00:01:28.080
♫ ♫

00:01:28.080 --> 00:01:31.400
♫ ♫

00:01:31.400 --> 00:01:35.000
♫ ♫

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:39.870
♫ ♫

00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:42.810
♫ ♫

00:01:42.810 --> 00:01:45.540
♫ ♫

00:01:45.540 --> 00:01:50.750
♫ ♫

00:01:56.400 --> 00:01:59.400
[Episode 2: Let's be best friends, okay?]

00:02:00.660 --> 00:02:02.038
- Senior.
- You're here too?

00:02:02.038 --> 00:02:03.660
Let's go.

00:02:09.680 --> 00:02:12.240
Hello, judges.

00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:15.280
I'm Li Ming, a freshman from the Law School.

00:02:15.280 --> 00:02:21.359
I'll be singing "Courage" by Fish Leong
for everyone.

00:02:21.359 --> 00:02:26.508
♪ We all need courage to face the rumors ♪

00:02:26.508 --> 00:02:31.120
♪ Finding the courage to hold you tight ♪

00:02:31.120 --> 00:02:34.470
♪ Our love is worth it ♪

00:02:34.470 --> 00:02:37.300
Okay, that's enough.

00:02:37.300 --> 00:02:38.699
Wait, Professor!

00:02:38.699 --> 00:02:41.472
It's just... what I had for dinner
was a bit too salty.

00:02:41.472 --> 00:02:43.180
I-I don't usually sound like this.

00:02:43.180 --> 00:02:45.300
Professor, could I have one more chance?

00:02:45.300 --> 00:02:48.200
That won't be necessary. Thanks for coming.

00:02:57.720 --> 00:02:59.199
You're done?

00:02:59.199 --> 00:03:01.039
How'd it go?

00:03:01.039 --> 00:03:05.280
Me? I just read a poem and blew them away.

00:03:05.280 --> 00:03:07.971
You should've seen it.
The judge held my hand and said,

00:03:07.971 --> 00:03:12.759
"Yu Lei, we've been waiting so long for you!"

00:03:13.280 --> 00:03:15.480
Passing was a piece of cake.

00:03:15.480 --> 00:03:18.799
By the way, what were you laughing at?

00:03:18.799 --> 00:03:22.039
It's just the students auditioning today.

00:03:22.039 --> 00:03:24.880
They're awful.
There was this one guy who was even worse.

00:03:24.880 --> 00:03:28.979
He looked like a gorilla and sang "Courage".

00:03:28.979 --> 00:03:33.060
I have no idea who gave him the courage
to sing that badly.

00:03:35.160 --> 00:03:37.319
And then there was this guy
who looked like a poodle.

00:03:37.319 --> 00:03:38.840
He tried to break dance,

00:03:38.840 --> 00:03:41.920
but as soon as he got on stage,
he just fell flat on his face.

00:03:41.920 --> 00:03:44.679
That was a floor move! You clearly don't know anything.

00:03:44.679 --> 00:03:46.580
Floor move? More like mopping the floor.

00:03:46.580 --> 00:03:48.080
You...

00:03:49.479 --> 00:03:52.880
Li Ming, Ouyang Han,
both of you just drop it.

00:03:52.880 --> 00:03:53.941
What?

00:03:53.941 --> 00:03:55.839
- You know each other?
- You know each other?

00:03:57.359 --> 00:04:00.539
Li Ming, this is my friend Ouyang Han.

00:04:00.539 --> 00:04:04.091
Ouyang Han, this is my friend Li Ming.

00:04:04.680 --> 00:04:06.240
We're all on the same side here.

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:07.799
Just consider this
a rough start to a friendship.

00:04:07.799 --> 00:04:10.539
Who'd want to be friends with him?

00:04:12.079 --> 00:04:13.960
Next! Instrument Group, Number 6.

00:04:13.960 --> 00:04:16.700
Chen Ke from the Law School,
please get ready.

00:05:09.654 --> 00:05:11.044
[Scoring rubrics]

00:05:27.120 --> 00:05:29.299
Now this is real music.

00:05:29.920 --> 00:05:32.000
Chen Ke is the man!

00:05:33.199 --> 00:05:36.159
I guess even a gorilla
can appreciate the finer things.

00:05:36.159 --> 00:05:37.920
It's called art.

00:05:37.920 --> 00:05:39.619
Like a poodle would know.

00:05:39.619 --> 00:05:43.360
Yu Lei, how do you stand his bad breath
every single day?

00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:45.260
You're the one with bad breath!

00:05:45.260 --> 00:05:46.460
No, you!

00:05:46.460 --> 00:05:47.681
- You!
- You!

00:05:47.681 --> 00:05:50.219
I didn't realize Chen Ke actually had talent.

00:05:50.219 --> 00:05:52.040
I totally underestimated him.

00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:55.600
But why does that piece sound so familiar?

00:05:55.600 --> 00:05:58.519
Have I heard it somewhere before?

00:06:00.839 --> 00:06:02.380
The list is out!

00:06:02.380 --> 00:06:03.842
- Li Fei Hang and Chen Ke are on it.
- It's here.

00:06:03.842 --> 00:06:05.680
Wait, why is my roommate on there?

00:06:05.680 --> 00:06:08.120
How did he make the cut?

00:06:08.120 --> 00:06:09.759
I can't believe I'm not on the list.

00:06:09.759 --> 00:06:13.160
These judges have no taste.

00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:16.440
Yu Lei, you're right here.

00:06:16.440 --> 00:06:18.360
Under the hosts.

00:06:18.360 --> 00:06:21.740
Well, I guess they aren't that blind
after all.

00:06:25.159 --> 00:06:28.159
Look, Chen Ke.

00:06:28.159 --> 00:06:30.619
No surprise there.

00:06:30.619 --> 00:06:33.539
I mean, he is actually good.

00:06:33.539 --> 00:06:36.839
But still, even if he's some piano prodigy,

00:06:36.839 --> 00:06:41.639
he's still not going to outshine
a handsome host like me.

00:06:43.600 --> 00:06:45.460
What's that supposed to mean?

00:07:47.140 --> 00:07:49.279
Yu Lei?

00:07:49.279 --> 00:07:51.240
Were you looking for me?

00:07:51.240 --> 00:07:53.399
No, I was just passing by.

00:07:53.399 --> 00:07:55.560
I'm not bothering you, am I?

00:07:55.560 --> 00:07:56.800
Not at all.

00:07:56.800 --> 00:08:00.319
By the way, is your foot all healed up?

00:08:02.431 --> 00:08:04.611
It's been fine for a while.

00:08:08.859 --> 00:08:11.959
Anyway, that piece you were playing
was really nice.

00:08:11.959 --> 00:08:14.040
What's it called?

00:08:14.040 --> 00:08:17.480
This? It's Beethoven's "Moonlight Sonata",
the first movement.

00:08:17.480 --> 00:08:19.440
Why? Do you like it?

00:08:19.440 --> 00:08:21.299
I can lend you the tape sometime.

00:08:21.299 --> 00:08:24.219
Oh, no, I'd feel bad.

00:08:25.319 --> 00:08:29.199
Well, actually, how about I just make a copy
and give it right back?

00:08:29.199 --> 00:08:31.319
It's fine.
It's hard to find a kindred spirit.

00:08:31.319 --> 00:08:33.720
Besides, I've had this tape forever.

00:08:33.720 --> 00:08:35.639
You can have it.

00:08:35.639 --> 00:08:36.978
Thanks, I appreciate it.

00:08:36.978 --> 00:08:40.579
So, why were you asking about this piece?

00:08:40.579 --> 00:08:43.159
I don't know. I just feel like
I've heard it somewhere before.

00:08:43.159 --> 00:08:47.159
It's familiar, but I can't place it.

00:08:48.039 --> 00:08:51.279
It feels like it has some kind of
special meaning to me.

00:08:51.279 --> 00:08:52.759
Really?

00:08:52.759 --> 00:08:56.639
It has a special meaning to me, too.

00:09:01.919 --> 00:09:03.880
- Grandma?
- Yes?

00:09:03.880 --> 00:09:07.240
Where is that sound coming from?

00:09:07.240 --> 00:09:09.812
It's coming from inside here.

00:09:09.812 --> 00:09:11.600
Oh, I know!

00:09:11.600 --> 00:09:15.840
There must be a little person living inside.

00:09:15.840 --> 00:09:19.504
And when I press this, they start singing.

00:09:19.504 --> 00:09:21.603
You're so smart.

00:09:22.480 --> 00:09:25.240
Here, press this key.

00:09:34.759 --> 00:09:36.320
That was my grandmother.

00:09:36.320 --> 00:09:39.840
The "Moonlight Sonata"
was her favorite piece.

00:09:39.840 --> 00:09:42.561
She's the one who taught me
my very first song on the piano.

00:09:44.159 --> 00:09:46.559
Oh, and she was a graduate
of Mingde University, too.

00:09:46.559 --> 00:09:48.120
Really?

00:09:48.120 --> 00:09:50.340
So she's an alumna!

00:09:50.340 --> 00:09:52.620
So, where is she now?

00:09:53.279 --> 00:09:56.524
Actually... she passed away.

00:09:57.000 --> 00:10:00.360
But I think if I can perform
her favorite piece

00:10:00.360 --> 00:10:02.919
on the stage here at Mingde University,

00:10:02.919 --> 00:10:04.080
maybe it'll make up for the fact

00:10:04.080 --> 00:10:07.299
that she never got the chance
to perform here herself.

00:10:11.799 --> 00:10:13.119
Oh, right.

00:10:13.119 --> 00:10:14.559
That was my grandma.

00:10:14.559 --> 00:10:16.320
The "Moonlight Sonata".

00:10:16.320 --> 00:10:18.280
I got it on tape.

00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:22.020
It's okay.

00:10:23.080 --> 00:10:24.240
Wait, what?

00:10:24.240 --> 00:10:27.159
I can't believe you actually
talked to Chen Ke for that long.

00:10:27.159 --> 00:10:29.840
I thought you two were enemies.

00:10:29.840 --> 00:10:31.220
We are.

00:10:31.220 --> 00:10:33.080
But he helped me out before.

00:10:33.080 --> 00:10:36.600
If I don't find a way to return the favor,

00:10:36.600 --> 00:10:39.520
I'll feel too guilty
to keep competing with him.

00:10:40.480 --> 00:10:41.993
Whatever.

00:10:41.993 --> 00:10:44.080
Let's just call it a temporary truce.

00:10:44.080 --> 00:10:46.740
Well, it's not like he's competing with you.

00:10:46.740 --> 00:10:48.279
Yu Lei!

00:10:48.279 --> 00:10:50.639
- Yu Lei! I was looking everywhere for you.
- What's wrong?

00:10:50.639 --> 00:10:52.919
Here's the updated program for the gala.

00:10:52.919 --> 00:10:54.399
There have been a lot of changes,

00:10:54.399 --> 00:10:57.699
so we'll need to rewrite the intros.

00:11:00.480 --> 00:11:02.720
Chen Ke's performance has been cut?

00:11:03.600 --> 00:11:05.240
Fine, let's do that.

00:11:05.240 --> 00:11:06.840
Okay.

00:11:10.960 --> 00:11:14.320
Sis, you're the one who
invited Chen Ke to the gala.

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:16.439
Why would you suddenly cut his performance?

00:11:16.439 --> 00:11:18.360
You have to give him an explanation.

00:11:18.360 --> 00:11:20.200
I did invite him,

00:11:20.200 --> 00:11:22.439
but cutting the act wasn't my decision.

00:11:22.439 --> 00:11:26.720
We originally had two piano pieces
and my violin solo.

00:11:26.720 --> 00:11:29.039
The administration felt
there were too many instrumentals,

00:11:29.039 --> 00:11:30.600
so they decided to cut one.

00:11:30.600 --> 00:11:32.639
But why did they have to cut Chen Ke's?

00:11:32.639 --> 00:11:34.559
Why not someone else's?

00:11:34.559 --> 00:11:36.759
Why do you think?

00:11:36.759 --> 00:11:38.240
It's totally rigged!

00:11:38.240 --> 00:11:41.039
Sis, you're the Student Union President.

00:11:41.039 --> 00:11:43.860
Can't you do something about this?

00:11:45.159 --> 00:11:47.639
Look, the administration
already made the call.

00:11:47.639 --> 00:11:49.679
But at least your hosting gig is safe.

00:11:49.679 --> 00:11:51.819
The higher-ups really like you.

00:11:54.200 --> 00:11:57.400
Since when did you start
caring so much about this?

00:11:58.140 --> 00:12:00.900
We're in the same class, that's all.

00:12:00.900 --> 00:12:03.300
Anyway, I've gotta go. See ya.

00:12:03.300 --> 00:12:04.921
Okay.

00:12:20.840 --> 00:12:22.639
I thought you guys weren't back yet.

00:12:22.639 --> 00:12:24.080
Perfect.

00:12:24.080 --> 00:12:26.020
Were you looking for me?

00:12:26.919 --> 00:12:28.559
Here, like I promised.

00:12:28.559 --> 00:12:31.519
Here. This is the recording my grandmother made.

00:12:31.519 --> 00:12:34.360
No, I can't take this.
It's too precious to you.

00:12:34.360 --> 00:12:36.480
It's fine. I just made a copy for you.

00:12:36.480 --> 00:12:38.439
Here.

00:12:38.439 --> 00:12:40.379
Thank you...

00:12:45.799 --> 00:12:48.519
Director, please reconsider.

00:12:49.240 --> 00:12:52.200
That student, really,
he's been practicing for so long.

00:12:52.200 --> 00:12:56.299
Look, Yu Lei,

00:12:56.299 --> 00:12:57.919
I'll say it again.

00:12:57.919 --> 00:12:59.480
This isn't about personal preference.

00:12:59.480 --> 00:13:02.880
It's about the big picture. The big picture.

00:13:02.880 --> 00:13:04.480
The big picture.

00:13:04.480 --> 00:13:07.840
Does "the big picture" always have to come
at someone else's expense?

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:11.519
Look, we have to keep the show
within the time limit.

00:13:11.519 --> 00:13:15.960
If you want to add a segment,
we have to cut one.

00:13:15.960 --> 00:13:19.079
So, who do you suggest we cut instead?

00:13:19.079 --> 00:13:20.399
I...

00:13:20.399 --> 00:13:22.519
Think about it.

00:13:25.539 --> 00:13:27.559
I could step down as host.

00:13:27.559 --> 00:13:30.851
If there's one less host,
would that save enough time?

00:13:31.439 --> 00:13:33.319
Let me think about it.

00:13:50.840 --> 00:13:52.360
Oh, good, you're here.

00:13:52.360 --> 00:13:54.120
Here's the latest program.

00:13:54.120 --> 00:13:56.200
Apparently, they changed it again.

00:13:56.200 --> 00:13:57.679
They're unbelievable.

00:13:57.679 --> 00:13:58.799
They change the script every day.

00:13:58.799 --> 00:14:02.080
I didn't even get to watch
"Happy Camp" this weekend.

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:05.642
Yeah!

00:14:06.360 --> 00:14:09.840
Yu Lei, why are you so happy?

00:14:09.840 --> 00:14:12.740
Isn't all this rewriting exhausting?

00:14:15.679 --> 00:14:18.200
Wait, why did it change
from a solo to a duet?

00:14:18.200 --> 00:14:21.980
The production team felt
the gala needed more variety.

00:14:21.980 --> 00:14:24.525
That's why they decided
to have us perform together.

00:14:24.525 --> 00:14:26.360
Don't read too much into it.

00:14:26.360 --> 00:14:30.536
No, actually,
I'm just happy I still get to perform.

00:14:30.536 --> 00:14:33.626
It's just... I rarely play with others.

00:14:33.626 --> 00:14:35.436
I hope I don't mess up the performance.

00:14:35.436 --> 00:14:38.292
It'll be fine.
We'll just practice a few times.

00:14:38.292 --> 00:14:40.256
I've prepared Chopin's
"Nocturne Op. 9 No. 2".

00:14:40.256 --> 00:14:44.585
Are you familiar with it?
If not, we can pick something else.

00:14:48.046 --> 00:14:49.392
I think I can manage.

00:14:49.392 --> 00:14:50.466
Great.

00:14:50.466 --> 00:14:52.703
Then let's try playing it together now.

00:14:52.703 --> 00:14:55.344
- Okay.
- Let's see how it feels.

00:15:19.960 --> 00:15:24.860
So, why do you think Zhang Han
is performing with a freshman?

00:15:24.860 --> 00:15:27.579
Yu Lei, are they really close?

00:15:27.579 --> 00:15:28.819
How should I know?

00:15:28.819 --> 00:15:32.165
Well, I heard Chen Ke is a total heartthrob.

00:15:32.165 --> 00:15:34.360
And playing Chopin's "Nocturne" together?

00:15:34.360 --> 00:15:36.480
There's definitely something
going on between them.

00:15:36.480 --> 00:15:38.699
Maybe they'll... Don't you think?

00:15:38.699 --> 00:15:40.539
Think what?

00:15:40.539 --> 00:15:41.799
Don't be dense.

00:15:41.799 --> 00:15:43.320
Look at Zhang Han...

00:15:43.320 --> 00:15:46.120
She's beautiful and a great violinist.

00:15:46.120 --> 00:15:49.939
And Chen Ke?
He's handsome and amazing on the piano.

00:15:49.939 --> 00:15:51.960
They're a match made in heaven.

00:15:51.960 --> 00:15:54.640
When you play music like that together,
things are bound to happen.

00:15:54.640 --> 00:15:56.799
- No way.
- Why not?

00:15:56.799 --> 00:15:58.819
It's totally impossible.

00:15:58.819 --> 00:16:00.360
There's an age gap!

00:16:00.360 --> 00:16:03.639
Look at Nicholas Tse and Faye Wong,
they're ten years apart.

00:16:03.639 --> 00:16:07.080
And they're still going strong.
It's so romantic.

00:16:07.080 --> 00:16:10.080
I'm so jealous.
I wish I had someone to hold hands with...

00:16:10.080 --> 00:16:12.159
And what are you two talking about?

00:16:12.159 --> 00:16:13.480
Don't get ahead of yourself.

00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:15.360
We're just talking about celebrity gossip.

00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:17.336
Oh, I see.

00:16:17.336 --> 00:16:18.659
Well, shall we...

00:16:18.659 --> 00:16:20.619
And what do you think it has to do with you?

00:16:20.619 --> 00:16:22.419
Come on.

00:16:51.479 --> 00:16:53.480
- Good.
- Oh, hello, Professor Meng.

00:16:53.480 --> 00:16:56.080
Was our practicing too loud?
Did we disturb you?

00:16:56.080 --> 00:16:57.120
No, not at all.

00:16:57.120 --> 00:16:59.880
It sounded so beautiful

00:16:59.880 --> 00:17:04.100
that I just found myself
following the music subconsciously.

00:17:06.280 --> 00:17:08.520
Sorry about that.
We'll keep it down next time.

00:17:08.520 --> 00:17:10.199
Don't worry about it.

00:17:10.199 --> 00:17:14.399
A scholar like me shouldn't stay cooped up
in a study all day anyway.

00:17:14.399 --> 00:17:17.439
I need to know what's going on in the world.

00:17:17.439 --> 00:17:22.379
Besides, what the two of you are making
is music, not noise.

00:17:22.959 --> 00:17:26.560
By the way, someone gave me these pastries,

00:17:26.560 --> 00:17:29.120
but I can't eat them
because of my blood sugar.

00:17:29.120 --> 00:17:31.288
So, I'm giving them to you two,

00:17:31.288 --> 00:17:35.239
as thanks to both of you
for the wonderful music.

00:17:35.239 --> 00:17:36.460
Here.

00:17:36.460 --> 00:17:37.560
Thank you, Professor Meng.

00:17:37.560 --> 00:17:39.260
You're very welcome.

00:17:56.880 --> 00:17:58.120
Sis!

00:17:58.120 --> 00:18:00.899
- Lei?
- Come here.

00:18:01.840 --> 00:18:06.600
Sis, your violin solo
is usually a school tradition, isn't it?

00:18:06.600 --> 00:18:09.040
Why'd you change it to a duet with Chen Ke?

00:18:09.040 --> 00:18:13.639
I had to make a small compromise
to keep everyone happy.

00:18:15.080 --> 00:18:17.679
Besides, didn't you go to
the administration yourself?

00:18:17.679 --> 00:18:21.639
You were even willing to give up hosting
just to save Chen Ke's act.

00:18:21.639 --> 00:18:25.040
Isn't everyone happy this way?

00:18:25.040 --> 00:18:27.679
That's only because he helped me out.

00:18:27.679 --> 00:18:31.120
I had to do something to return the favor.

00:18:31.120 --> 00:18:34.744
But that doesn't mean
you should have to lose out.

00:18:35.880 --> 00:18:37.239
Where is he, anyway?

00:18:37.239 --> 00:18:38.719
Why isn't he practicing with you?

00:18:38.719 --> 00:18:39.940
Is he throwing a fit?

00:18:39.940 --> 00:18:42.399
You're overthinking things.

00:18:42.399 --> 00:18:44.320
I'm not losing out at all.

00:18:44.320 --> 00:18:46.120
We've been practicing all afternoon.

00:18:46.120 --> 00:18:48.899
He just had to step out for a bit.

00:18:49.679 --> 00:18:52.042
Well, at least he's being professional.

00:18:52.042 --> 00:18:56.399
Actually,
I've had a bit of a surprise myself.

00:18:56.399 --> 00:18:59.040
I didn't expect us
to have such great chemistry

00:18:59.040 --> 00:19:01.400
the first time we played together.

00:19:02.199 --> 00:19:04.880
So you two are really in sync, huh?

00:19:04.880 --> 00:19:09.020
He's also very dedicated
and works hard on his own.

00:19:09.020 --> 00:19:13.199
You know, you could really
learn a thing or two from him.

00:19:13.199 --> 00:19:16.120
Wait, Sis, that's not fair.

00:19:16.120 --> 00:19:20.099
Why do you always find a way
to praise him while putting me down?

00:19:21.046 --> 00:19:23.399
I'm dedicated too!

00:19:23.399 --> 00:19:27.526
Besides, what's so great about
being wound up like that all the time?

00:19:27.526 --> 00:19:32.320
You need to strike a balance
between work and play.

00:19:32.320 --> 00:19:34.679
You have a point.

00:19:34.679 --> 00:19:36.959
Actually, the school is
showing a movie tonight.

00:19:36.959 --> 00:19:41.539
I bought two tickets
and was planning to invite Chen Ke.

00:19:41.539 --> 00:19:43.719
I thought it would help him relax.

00:19:43.719 --> 00:19:46.600
What? You're taking him to a movie?

00:19:46.600 --> 00:19:47.999
Yeah.

00:19:47.999 --> 00:19:50.159
That's basically a date!

00:19:50.159 --> 00:19:52.040
Sis, don't tell me you're
trying to be like Faye Wong.

00:19:52.040 --> 00:19:53.320
You're not actually into younger guys,
are you?

00:19:53.320 --> 00:19:54.679
This is crazy.

00:19:54.679 --> 00:19:56.880
- That's too much.
- Yu Lei!

00:19:56.880 --> 00:19:58.919
Aren't you supposed to be
a modern college student?

00:19:58.919 --> 00:20:00.159
It's just a movie.

00:20:00.159 --> 00:20:02.294
That doesn't mean we're dating.

00:20:02.760 --> 00:20:06.040
What's wrong with a senior
looking out for a junior?

00:20:06.040 --> 00:20:08.160
Everything is wrong with it.

00:20:08.160 --> 00:20:09.167
President!

00:20:09.167 --> 00:20:11.520
President, the committee
has some urgent business.

00:20:11.520 --> 00:20:15.040
They want to meet with
our department tonight. Here.

00:20:15.040 --> 00:20:16.120
Tonight?

00:20:16.120 --> 00:20:18.020
- Yeah.
- I...

00:20:18.020 --> 00:20:19.719
Sis, Sis!

00:20:19.719 --> 00:20:21.520
How about I go to the movie instead?

00:20:21.520 --> 00:20:24.780
The tickets are already bought,
it'd be a waste not to use them.

00:20:26.320 --> 00:20:27.360
Fine.

00:20:27.360 --> 00:20:28.999
I guess I'll let you have them.

00:20:28.999 --> 00:20:30.560
Lucky you.

00:20:30.560 --> 00:20:32.360
Great!

00:20:32.360 --> 00:20:33.385
Thanks, Sis.

00:20:33.385 --> 00:20:35.924
[Student's Club]

00:20:53.159 --> 00:20:55.640
Why isn't Senior here yet?

00:21:02.543 --> 00:21:05.200
Hey, Bo Ya. Waiting for your Zi Qi?
(*Figures in Chinese legend about friendship)

00:21:05.200 --> 00:21:08.160
Huh? What are you talking about?

00:21:09.040 --> 00:21:11.064
You know, "High Mountains and Flowing Water".

00:21:11.064 --> 00:21:12.679
Bo Ya and Zi Qi.

00:21:12.679 --> 00:21:16.399
Aren't you and my sister
like kindred spirits?

00:21:16.399 --> 00:21:19.840
If you're Bo Ya, then she must be your Zi Qi.

00:21:22.199 --> 00:21:27.439
Musically speaking,
I think we do have a certain connection.

00:21:27.439 --> 00:21:29.600
But as for anything else...

00:21:29.600 --> 00:21:32.920
I wouldn't go as far as calling us soulmates.

00:21:34.159 --> 00:21:35.199
What about me?

00:21:35.199 --> 00:21:37.360
Do I qualify as your Zi Qi?

00:21:38.239 --> 00:21:40.039
You're unbelievable.

00:21:40.999 --> 00:21:43.040
Anyway, I'll stop teasing.

00:21:43.040 --> 00:21:45.239
My sister had something come up
at the last minute,

00:21:45.239 --> 00:21:46.959
so she gave me her ticket.

00:21:46.959 --> 00:21:49.039
Come on, let's watch the movie.

00:22:27.120 --> 00:22:30.600
Chen Ke, you always act so serious.

00:22:30.600 --> 00:22:34.040
I can't believe you actually cried
during the movie.

00:22:34.040 --> 00:22:35.800
Look at your red nose!

00:22:35.800 --> 00:22:37.479
You were sobbing too.

00:22:37.479 --> 00:22:39.679
I heard you.

00:22:39.679 --> 00:22:41.560
I wasn't nearly as bad as you.

00:22:41.560 --> 00:22:45.679
You were twitching like a little squirrel.

00:22:45.679 --> 00:22:47.040
Get the hell out of here.

00:22:47.040 --> 00:22:49.479
If I'm a squirrel, then what are you?

00:22:49.479 --> 00:22:51.080
A devious old fox?

00:22:51.080 --> 00:22:52.399
Me?

00:22:52.399 --> 00:22:54.999
How am I an old fox?

00:22:54.999 --> 00:22:57.560
During that scene in the car,

00:22:57.560 --> 00:22:59.560
I didn't even know what was going on yet,

00:22:59.560 --> 00:23:01.840
but you were already laughing.

00:23:01.840 --> 00:23:03.479
You've got a dirty mind.

00:23:03.479 --> 00:23:05.840
And you say you're not an old fox?

00:23:06.999 --> 00:23:10.239
You're a pretty good-looking guy.

00:23:10.239 --> 00:23:12.040
Have you really never had a girlfriend?

00:23:12.040 --> 00:23:14.040
I don't buy that you're this innocent.

00:23:14.040 --> 00:23:16.120
It's not anything like that.

00:23:16.120 --> 00:23:17.959
I've only ever had one girlfriend.

00:23:17.959 --> 00:23:19.679
We didn't even kiss.

00:23:19.679 --> 00:23:22.120
The most we did was hold hands.

00:23:22.120 --> 00:23:23.542
Love?

00:23:23.542 --> 00:23:25.120
I don't think it was really love.

00:23:25.120 --> 00:23:28.519
It was probably just curiosity
about the opposite sex.

00:23:42.439 --> 00:23:44.360
Alright, level with me.

00:23:44.360 --> 00:23:46.560
Is there a girl you like right now?

00:23:46.560 --> 00:23:48.679
Right now?

00:23:48.679 --> 00:23:50.640
Not at the moment.

00:23:51.760 --> 00:23:55.575
Well, what's your type, then?

00:23:56.399 --> 00:23:59.399
I think we'd need to have common interests.

00:23:59.399 --> 00:24:02.920
A genuine, mutual attraction from the heart.

00:24:03.679 --> 00:24:06.560
So... what do you think of my sister?

00:24:06.560 --> 00:24:08.320
Why are you asking me that?

00:24:08.320 --> 00:24:09.954
Didn't you say the other day

00:24:09.954 --> 00:24:13.419
that whoever lost the game
wouldn't talk to her?

00:24:13.419 --> 00:24:16.679
I-I was just joking then.

00:24:16.679 --> 00:24:18.800
I'm just using her as an example.

00:24:18.800 --> 00:24:22.040
So all that time you were targeting me,

00:24:22.040 --> 00:24:24.372
it was because you were worried
about me and your sister?

00:24:25.239 --> 00:24:27.479
Don't worry. It's not like that.

00:24:27.479 --> 00:24:32.959
She's amazing,
but I just don't feel that way about her.

00:24:34.639 --> 00:24:36.208
What way?

00:24:38.239 --> 00:24:40.320
I remember a writer once said...

00:24:40.320 --> 00:24:44.479
"To me, love isn't just about
physical intimacy or sharing a meal.

00:24:44.479 --> 00:24:46.399
It's an undying desire...

00:24:46.399 --> 00:24:48.600
a heroic dream in a weary life."

00:24:48.600 --> 00:24:50.360
I've always loved that quote.

00:24:50.360 --> 00:24:52.959
I think that's what love should be.

00:24:52.959 --> 00:24:55.040
Something sacred.

00:24:55.040 --> 00:24:58.999
That's the "feeling" I'm talking about.

00:25:01.719 --> 00:25:06.399
I think that's true for everyone,
throughout history.

00:25:06.399 --> 00:25:07.600
It's like they say.

00:25:07.600 --> 00:25:09.840
"They talk of a match made in gold and jade,

00:25:09.840 --> 00:25:12.760
but I only dream of the old alliance
of wood and stone."

00:25:12.760 --> 00:25:14.560
A lot of people who read
"Dream of the Red Chamber"

00:25:14.560 --> 00:25:17.479
think Xue Bao Chai is smart and proper,

00:25:17.479 --> 00:25:20.039
so she's the best match for Jia Bao Yu.

00:25:20.679 --> 00:25:21.919
But I don't think so.

00:25:21.919 --> 00:25:23.760
Exactly.

00:25:23.760 --> 00:25:26.159
Bao Yu and Dai Yu are the ones
who truly belong together.

00:25:26.159 --> 00:25:28.999
They have a real soul connection.

00:25:28.999 --> 00:25:32.919
Some of those sequels
that force Bao Chai and Bao Yu together

00:25:32.919 --> 00:25:35.199
completely miss the point.

00:25:35.199 --> 00:25:38.040
Yeah. If Cao Xue Qin knew,

00:25:38.040 --> 00:25:41.080
he'd probably want to take them all out.

00:25:41.080 --> 00:25:43.600
He wasn't that hot-headed.

00:25:44.560 --> 00:25:47.999
But speaking of souls...

00:25:47.999 --> 00:25:50.959
how do you actually see someone's soul?

00:25:51.645 --> 00:25:55.679
Maybe it's because souls are so hard to see,

00:25:55.679 --> 00:26:01.999
so people have always lamented
how rare true love is.

00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:06.840
When someone has something on their mind,
they frown.

00:26:06.840 --> 00:26:08.960
Just like you're doing right now.

00:26:09.679 --> 00:26:13.639
I think seeing that frown
is like seeing into someone's soul.

00:26:13.639 --> 00:26:15.399
You're right.

00:26:15.399 --> 00:26:17.520
I think that's it.

00:26:17.520 --> 00:26:21.840
And I believe that beautiful souls
are naturally drawn to each other.

00:26:21.840 --> 00:26:24.719
They just keep getting closer.

00:26:24.719 --> 00:26:26.159
It's like that poem.

00:26:26.159 --> 00:26:29.639
"You're from Yunnan, Yuanmou."

00:26:29.639 --> 00:26:31.800
"I'm from Beijing, Zhoukou."

00:26:31.800 --> 00:26:34.959
- "We reach out our furry hands..."
- "And it's love..."

00:26:34.959 --> 00:26:38.120
- "That makes us walk upright like a pole."
- "That makes us walk upright like a pole."

00:26:41.679 --> 00:26:44.600
Chen Ke, I hope everything goes well.

00:26:44.600 --> 00:26:48.039
Wait, no. I mean,
I hope the performance is a huge success.

00:26:49.040 --> 00:26:50.840
It will be.

00:27:00.679 --> 00:27:03.760
September 2000. Sunny.

00:27:03.760 --> 00:27:06.320
Every day is busy and fulfilling.

00:27:06.320 --> 00:27:11.639
New people, new experiences...
My schedule is packed.

00:27:11.639 --> 00:27:15.560
As the performance draws closer,
I'm getting more and more excited.

00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:18.479
Not just to fulfill my grandmother's wish,

00:27:18.479 --> 00:27:21.560
but also to live up to
everyone's expectations.

00:27:21.560 --> 00:27:24.919
Like Senior... Professor Meng...

00:27:24.919 --> 00:27:28.199
and Yu Lei.

00:27:52.800 --> 00:27:55.480
[Mingde University 2000 Welcoming Gala]

00:27:55.480 --> 00:27:56.932
Wow, so handsome.

00:28:00.159 --> 00:28:02.320
Get out of my way.

00:28:02.320 --> 00:28:04.120
You're so childish.

00:28:11.959 --> 00:28:14.399
Chen Ke, you're up next.

00:28:14.399 --> 00:28:16.199
Good luck!

00:28:18.880 --> 00:28:21.279
Chen Ke, it's time for you to go on.

00:31:00.040 --> 00:31:04.959
♪ You ask me how deep my love is ♪

00:31:04.959 --> 00:31:06.439
♪ I love you as much as... ♪

00:31:06.439 --> 00:31:08.121
- Meng Yu, stop singing! Have a drink first.
- Coming.

00:31:08.121 --> 00:31:10.400
We'll have plenty of time for that later.
Come on.

00:31:10.400 --> 00:31:12.320
Let's all have a drink together.

00:31:12.320 --> 00:31:14.560
- Cheers!
- Come on. Everyone!

00:31:14.560 --> 00:31:17.519
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

00:31:21.855 --> 00:31:23.199
Bottoms up!

00:31:23.199 --> 00:31:26.999
Chen Ke, you did a great job at the gala.

00:31:26.999 --> 00:31:29.239
Senior, I'm the one who should be
thanking you.

00:31:29.239 --> 00:31:30.479
Sis!

00:31:30.479 --> 00:31:32.239
Why are you only praising Chen Ke?

00:31:32.239 --> 00:31:34.439
You didn't even mention my contribution.

00:31:34.439 --> 00:31:36.439
Oh, right. Chen Ke,
you probably didn't know this,

00:31:36.439 --> 00:31:39.880
but the administration
almost cut your piano piece.

00:31:39.880 --> 00:31:42.760
It was all thanks to our Lei.
He fought so hard for you.

00:31:42.760 --> 00:31:44.959
That's the only reason
we got to perform together.

00:31:44.959 --> 00:31:46.639
If you're going to thank anyone, thank him.

00:31:46.639 --> 00:31:48.959
Well, thank you both, then.

00:31:49.959 --> 00:31:51.439
Easy there.

00:31:51.439 --> 00:31:52.840
Wow, look at him go.

00:31:52.840 --> 00:31:55.800
- Nice!
- Take it easy.

00:31:55.800 --> 00:31:58.120
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

00:32:00.560 --> 00:32:02.800
Sis, I can handle this.

00:32:02.800 --> 00:32:04.880
You're being way too sincere.

00:32:04.880 --> 00:32:06.639
You're such a good kid.

00:32:06.639 --> 00:32:10.280
Yu Lei, I want to thank you
on behalf of my grandmother, too.

00:32:11.120 --> 00:32:12.920
Don't mention it.

00:32:14.120 --> 00:32:16.679
Director. We all worked hard, too.

00:32:16.679 --> 00:32:18.760
Why are you only paying attention to them?

00:32:18.760 --> 00:32:20.399
One at a time, Meng Yu.

00:32:20.399 --> 00:32:21.719
You were great, too.

00:32:21.719 --> 00:32:24.600
Tell you what. National Day is coming up.

00:32:24.600 --> 00:32:26.159
Let's all go on a trip together.

00:32:26.159 --> 00:32:28.199
Anyone who's free can come,
and you can bring friends.

00:32:28.199 --> 00:32:29.418
- Sounds good!
- Really?

00:32:29.418 --> 00:32:31.159
- Long live the senior!
- Come on, everyone!

00:32:31.159 --> 00:32:32.601
Let's go! Trip time!

00:32:32.601 --> 00:32:34.840
Cheers!

00:32:45.960 --> 00:32:52.254
[Mingde University celebrates
the National Day holiday]

00:32:53.439 --> 00:32:55.560
Wow, he's so handsome!

00:32:55.560 --> 00:32:57.159
Look.

00:32:57.159 --> 00:32:59.560
Isn't he handsome?

00:32:59.560 --> 00:33:00.719
Here, you can have this one.

00:33:00.719 --> 00:33:02.320
This one's really cool, too.

00:33:02.320 --> 00:33:03.760
No way!

00:33:03.760 --> 00:33:05.199
- Which one do you like best?
- Why are you being like that?

00:33:05.199 --> 00:33:07.120
- You're so stingy.
- Look at this one.

00:33:07.120 --> 00:33:08.840
Stingy?

00:33:08.840 --> 00:33:11.840
I think you're the one with the nerve
to just tag along.

00:33:11.840 --> 00:33:14.479
I have no idea why you even came.

00:33:14.479 --> 00:33:17.360
Hey, I helped set up the stage
for the school, okay?

00:33:17.360 --> 00:33:19.336
Why shouldn't I be allowed to come?

00:33:20.040 --> 00:33:21.920
Besides...

00:33:23.374 --> 00:33:25.080
There are plenty of pretty girls here.

00:33:25.080 --> 00:33:26.601
Isn't that why you're here, too?

00:33:27.320 --> 00:33:28.880
You're delusional.

00:33:28.880 --> 00:33:30.520
You think everyone is
as girl-crazy as you are?

00:33:30.520 --> 00:33:32.156
Pervert.

00:33:32.840 --> 00:33:34.639
Yu Lei invited me.

00:33:34.639 --> 00:33:37.239
I'm basically family.

00:33:37.239 --> 00:33:39.760
Family?

00:33:39.760 --> 00:33:41.360
You look more like a rat to me.

00:33:41.360 --> 00:33:43.160
You...

00:33:44.719 --> 00:33:46.519
Yu Lei, here.

00:33:49.360 --> 00:33:53.199
Yu Lei, how are we splitting up the rooms
at the guesthouse?

00:33:53.199 --> 00:33:55.360
Senior, why don't we share a room?

00:33:55.360 --> 00:33:56.731
Sounds good.

00:33:57.719 --> 00:34:00.719
Yu Lei! Let's share a room.

00:34:00.719 --> 00:34:04.249
Sorry, I already told Chen Ke
I'd stay with him.

00:34:04.249 --> 00:34:07.279
Huh? Wait, when did we agree to that?

00:34:10.360 --> 00:34:14.320
Chen Ke keeps saying
he doesn't have feelings for my sister,

00:34:14.320 --> 00:34:16.320
but you never know.

00:34:16.320 --> 00:34:19.999
During this trip,
I need to keep a close eye on him.

00:34:19.999 --> 00:34:22.240
Our bus is here. Let's go.

00:34:22.240 --> 00:34:24.600
- Let's go, let's go!
- Let's go, let's go!

00:34:26.760 --> 00:34:28.039
Looks like you've been dumped.

00:34:28.039 --> 00:34:29.519
Feeling a bit left out?

00:34:29.519 --> 00:34:31.319
Get lost.

00:34:32.039 --> 00:34:36.097
Fine. I'll be generous
and let you stay in my room.

00:34:36.880 --> 00:34:38.680
You must be dreaming.

00:34:38.680 --> 00:34:41.560
Who knows if you snore like crazy?

00:34:42.240 --> 00:34:44.800
You're so ungrateful.

00:34:44.800 --> 00:34:47.560
Just get in there. Stop stalling.

00:36:35.559 --> 00:36:38.839
Yu Lei, what took you so long in the shower?

00:36:39.880 --> 00:36:41.680
Did I take that long?

00:36:41.680 --> 00:36:43.480
It's your turn.

00:36:45.200 --> 00:36:46.479
Hey.

00:36:46.479 --> 00:36:48.399
Why didn't you dry your hair?

00:36:48.399 --> 00:36:51.399
There's a fan right there.
You're going to catch a cold.

00:36:51.399 --> 00:36:54.439
It's fine. I'll just let it air dry.

00:36:54.439 --> 00:36:56.520
You can't do that.

00:36:59.999 --> 00:37:01.799
Yu Lei!

00:37:02.840 --> 00:37:04.519
You guys have to let me stay here tonight,

00:37:04.519 --> 00:37:06.240
or I'm not going to make it.

00:37:06.240 --> 00:37:07.599
What's wrong now?

00:37:07.599 --> 00:37:08.840
Li Ming!

00:37:08.840 --> 00:37:10.640
He was out the second his head
hit the pillow.

00:37:10.640 --> 00:37:12.039
And he snores!

00:37:12.039 --> 00:37:14.800
It sounds like a thunderstorm in there.

00:37:14.800 --> 00:37:17.519
I think I'm going deaf.

00:37:17.519 --> 00:37:20.240
But... this is just a single bed.

00:37:20.240 --> 00:37:22.919
It's not big enough for two people.

00:37:22.919 --> 00:37:25.559
I promise I'll be good.

00:37:25.559 --> 00:37:26.800
I won't even move.

00:37:26.800 --> 00:37:28.519
Just let me crash here for one night.

00:37:28.519 --> 00:37:30.919
Please, Yu Lei?

00:37:31.720 --> 00:37:33.559
What about the sofa in the living room?

00:37:33.559 --> 00:37:36.799
I already checked. It's too drafty out there.

00:37:37.479 --> 00:37:40.160
Tell you what... you two take the room,

00:37:40.160 --> 00:37:41.880
and I'll go sleep on the sofa.

00:37:41.880 --> 00:37:43.569
- Okay.
- No way.

00:37:50.511 --> 00:37:52.068
I'll go.

00:38:13.466 --> 00:38:16.517
[Museum of Cinema]

00:38:33.079 --> 00:38:36.240
What? Out for an early walk
without telling me?

00:38:36.240 --> 00:38:37.559
Look at those dark circles.

00:38:37.559 --> 00:38:39.599
Didn't you sleep well?

00:38:39.599 --> 00:38:40.919
Don't even get me started.

00:38:40.919 --> 00:38:43.320
I spent all night
in the living room shivering.

00:38:43.320 --> 00:38:46.025
I only managed to catch
a few minutes of sleep at dawn.

00:38:49.720 --> 00:38:52.439
What about you?
You look like you didn't sleep much either.

00:38:52.439 --> 00:38:56.001
I always have trouble sleeping
in a new environment.

00:38:56.001 --> 00:38:59.200
Plus, Ouyang Han wouldn't stop talking to me.

00:38:59.200 --> 00:39:01.800
Honestly, I really envy you sometimes.

00:39:01.800 --> 00:39:03.599
You have so many good friends,

00:39:03.599 --> 00:39:06.039
and they're all so full of life.

00:39:06.039 --> 00:39:07.839
Not like me.

00:39:11.079 --> 00:39:13.359
It's raining! Let's go.

00:39:29.880 --> 00:39:31.160
Oh, man.

00:39:31.160 --> 00:39:33.160
We were planning on going for a hike today.

00:39:33.160 --> 00:39:35.600
I guess that's not happening.

00:40:10.200 --> 00:40:13.839
Damn. It looks like
the rain is getting heavier.

00:40:14.800 --> 00:40:17.480
Let's just run for it!

00:40:21.967 --> 00:40:23.767
Come on!

00:40:31.959 --> 00:40:34.919
Cheers!

00:40:37.119 --> 00:40:39.240
This is actually really good.

00:40:39.240 --> 00:40:41.680
- Is it ready yet? Let me see.
- The water isn't boiling yet.

00:40:41.680 --> 00:40:42.800
We can't put the food in.

00:40:42.800 --> 00:40:45.559
- Not yet.
- Just wait a bit.

00:40:45.559 --> 00:40:47.680
How about we watch a movie first?

00:40:47.680 --> 00:40:48.680
Sure.

00:40:48.680 --> 00:40:49.919
What do you have?

00:40:49.919 --> 00:40:51.399
Any Hollywood blockbusters?

00:40:51.399 --> 00:40:53.519
I heard "Mission: Impossible 2"
is really good.

00:40:53.519 --> 00:40:56.240
Tom Cruise is so hot.

00:40:56.240 --> 00:40:58.042
I don't have that.

00:40:58.760 --> 00:40:59.840
But I do have this.

00:40:59.840 --> 00:41:01.024
Why don't we watch this?
[Happy Together]

00:41:01.024 --> 00:41:02.640
(*one of the most depressing gay movies
ever made)

00:41:02.640 --> 00:41:04.919
It's got Leslie Cheung and Tony Leung.

00:41:04.919 --> 00:41:06.079
There are a lot of stars in it.

00:41:06.079 --> 00:41:08.279
- Sounds good!
- Let's do it.

00:41:13.760 --> 00:41:14.825
Put the food in!

00:41:14.825 --> 00:41:16.149
Okay.

00:41:28.822 --> 00:41:32.160
Wait... is this a porno?

00:41:34.959 --> 00:41:37.240
Why are there two guys?

00:41:37.240 --> 00:41:39.720
Leslie Cheung and Tony Leung were in this?

00:41:40.640 --> 00:41:43.079
Did the shopkeeper give us the wrong tape?

00:41:43.079 --> 00:41:45.040
I thought...

00:41:51.760 --> 00:41:53.160
Hey, why don't we just watch this instead?

00:41:53.160 --> 00:41:56.079
"King of Comedy". It'll be more fun.

00:41:56.079 --> 00:41:59.000
Yeah, "King of Comedy" is great.

00:42:00.599 --> 00:42:02.200
Hurry up, Yu Lei!

00:42:02.200 --> 00:42:04.039
Come on, Yu Lei.

00:42:04.039 --> 00:42:06.919
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

00:42:36.320 --> 00:42:38.720
Why'd you stop eating?

00:42:38.720 --> 00:42:39.720
I don't know.

00:42:39.720 --> 00:42:42.840
Between the beer and the hot pot...

00:42:42.840 --> 00:42:43.999
Look.

00:42:43.999 --> 00:42:46.039
I feel like my stomach is about to explode.

00:42:46.039 --> 00:42:47.839
That's ridiculous.

00:42:48.479 --> 00:42:49.800
You don't have a stomach.

00:42:49.800 --> 00:42:51.719
Those are abs.

00:43:01.200 --> 00:43:07.160
Yu Lei, do you ever feel like I'm not normal?

00:43:07.160 --> 00:43:10.880
Everyone else is out chasing the sun,
but I...

00:43:10.880 --> 00:43:13.399
I'm always alone in the dark.

00:43:15.119 --> 00:43:18.359
Chen Ke, what are you talking about?

00:43:19.479 --> 00:43:24.119
Yu Lei, you know, when I was a kid,

00:43:24.119 --> 00:43:25.880
it was just me and my grandmother.

00:43:25.880 --> 00:43:29.079
Between practicing and competitions,

00:43:29.079 --> 00:43:32.039
I never had time to talk
to people my own age.

00:43:32.039 --> 00:43:36.399
I didn't even know
how to act around other kids.

00:43:36.399 --> 00:43:40.239
After a while,
I just got used to being by myself.

00:43:41.320 --> 00:43:45.680
So... I've been following you around
this whole time.

00:43:45.680 --> 00:43:48.160
Do you find me annoying?

00:43:51.228 --> 00:43:52.519
Get drunk!

00:43:52.519 --> 00:43:54.640
Let's go.

00:43:57.160 --> 00:43:58.640
No.

00:43:58.640 --> 00:44:00.519
Actually, I like it.

00:44:00.519 --> 00:44:04.320
I'm happy to tell you about myself.

00:44:04.320 --> 00:44:06.999
I even find myself thinking...

00:44:06.999 --> 00:44:09.039
that I wish I'd met you sooner.

00:44:09.039 --> 00:44:13.000
Maybe then, I wouldn't have spent
my whole life without any friends.

00:44:16.559 --> 00:44:18.919
Chen Ke, I'm sorry.

00:44:18.919 --> 00:44:20.759
To be honest...

00:44:22.720 --> 00:44:27.599
To be honest, I used to think
you were just this cold, difficult person.

00:44:27.599 --> 00:44:30.919
That's why I couldn't stand you.

00:44:30.919 --> 00:44:33.880
But then I realized...

00:44:33.880 --> 00:44:35.975
that's not who you are at all.

00:44:36.720 --> 00:44:38.320
It's okay.

00:44:38.320 --> 00:44:42.039
I'm used to people
getting the wrong idea about me.

00:44:42.039 --> 00:44:47.800
I always felt like people would come and go,

00:44:47.800 --> 00:44:50.799
and in the end, I'd always be alone.

00:44:51.439 --> 00:44:55.680
But when I'm with you, I don't feel that way.

00:45:05.399 --> 00:45:06.519
Look.

00:45:06.519 --> 00:45:09.560
Even the rain has taken on meaning now.

00:45:14.720 --> 00:45:16.999
Yu Lei...

00:45:16.999 --> 00:45:20.808
can I consider you my friend?

00:45:22.880 --> 00:45:26.359
No. My best friend.

00:45:27.360 --> 00:45:29.319
Is that okay?

00:45:31.640 --> 00:45:33.440
- Sure.
- Here.

00:45:34.360 --> 00:45:36.160
Pinky swear.

00:46:42.825 --> 00:46:45.200
- Chen Ke...
- That night,

00:46:45.200 --> 00:46:48.680
I couldn't take my eyes off Chen Ke's face.

00:46:48.680 --> 00:46:51.720
I suddenly realized how cute he actually was.

00:46:51.720 --> 00:46:55.240
I felt this sudden urge
to be even closer to him.

00:46:55.240 --> 00:46:58.399
It was only later that it finally clicked.

00:46:58.399 --> 00:47:00.970
- That was when I started falling for him.
- Goodnight.

00:47:05.280 --> 00:47:07.160
[Next Episode]
Lately, you and Chen Ke

00:47:07.160 --> 00:47:09.640
have been joined at the hip, haven't you?

00:47:09.640 --> 00:47:12.119
I thought you'd completely
forgotten about me.

00:47:12.119 --> 00:47:15.800
Do you want to try the pose I mentioned?

00:47:15.800 --> 00:47:17.680
What pose?

00:47:18.599 --> 00:47:20.360
Are you free on Christmas?

00:47:20.360 --> 00:47:21.680
I...

00:47:22.479 --> 00:47:23.880
Christmas?

00:47:23.880 --> 00:47:26.407
I might have some plans of my own.

00:47:26.407 --> 00:47:29.519
Is romance the only way to be intimate?

00:47:29.519 --> 00:47:33.160
Can't friends, brothers,
or family be close, too?

00:47:33.160 --> 00:47:35.280
Can't we express that physically?